To implement a trait in Rust, you use the `impl` keyword followed by the trait name for your type.

Example:
```rust
trait Greet {
    fn greet(&self) -> String;
}

struct Person {
    name: String,
}

impl Greet for Person {
    fn greet(&self) -> String {
        format!("Hello, {}!", self.name)
    }
}
```
